article_title: Canada Factory Shipments Advanced 2.3% in January
article_text:
OTTAWA—Canadian factory sales rose in January on​robust car shipments, beating expectations and marking the latest in a series of positive readings​on the nonresource side of the country’s economy, which has been hard hit by the commodity-price rout.

The value of factory sales rose 2.3% month-over-month to a record 53.13 billion Canadian dollars (about $39.76 billion), Statistics Canada said Wednesday. That was the third-straight increase in manufacturing sales, and well ahead of the 0.5% gain economists expected,...
